<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,152,990]" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,615,641]" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<emphasis box="[626,756,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">G. d i s t i g m a</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[767,861,615,641]" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">sp. nov.</emphasis>
in both external and genital characters. It can be distinguished by following: in external characters, this species only with 
<number box="[1043,1058,654,680]" pageId="14" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
black spot on marginal area of forewing, while 
<emphasis box="[345,475,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">G. d i s t i g m a</emphasis>
has 
<number box="[533,548,693,719]" pageId="14" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
spots; in male genitalia, this species with a small spine-like cornutus while without cornutus in latter, the species with the width of valva much narrower than 
<taxonomicName box="[1140,1275,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Gargela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distigma">
<emphasis box="[1140,1275,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">G. distigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the shape of juxta and the costal arm are absolutely different. Additonally, in female genitalia, it is very difficult to be distinguished with 
<taxonomicName box="[382,520,809,834]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Gargela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albidusa">
<emphasis box="[382,520,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">G. albidusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except this species has the ductus bursae folded near corpus bursae; on the other side, 
<taxonomicName box="[280,412,848,873]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Gargela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albidusa">
<emphasis box="[280,412,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">G. albidusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the middle and submarginal lines absent or indistinct while this species has the two lines both clear.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="54" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,152,990]" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,343,925,951]" pageId="14" pageNumber="54">Etymology.</emphasis>
